Create the Shape map 13

While creating the map ensure the To enable Shape Map, select File > Options and Settings > Options > Preview Features, then select the Shape Map Visual checkbox.

You'll need to restart Power BI Desktop after you make the selection. Once Shape Map is enabled, select the Shape Map icon from the Visualizations pane.

X: 283

Y: 147

W: 656

H:  421


Title - on, Tooltip - on, Value color - #FFFFFF, Label color - #C8C8C8, Visual header - on, diverging - on (Min color -#DEEFF, Center color - #a8337d, Max color - #118DFF.

To create title and title background -Title - on, Title background -#0d6abf,   title font - #ffffff,  Title text size -18, Title Alignment - Center, category -off, word wrap -on, border on

On step number

On step number 6. take a screenshot of the diverging colors save the image and add it on the map by selecting add image and position it under the map. Create a text box and type in L(Low) and H (High)  set the diverging colors to minimum - #DEEFFF , Center -#a8337d , Maximum-#118DFF

Under format. on the default color -ON, Set the default color to #c8c6cH
